<paragraph id="391436C8FF97B058FF2DFC12FE65FB95" blockId="11.[132,1237,905,1791]" pageId="11">
EMENDED DIAGNOSIS: 
<taxonomicName id="FEAB4D4BFF97B058FE24FC11FD17FBD8" box="[445,653,1017,1043]" class="Trilobita" family="Olenidae" genus="Cloacaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="0BDFEADAFF97B058FE24FC11FDAFFBD8" box="[445,565,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="11">Cloacaspis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with greater (sag., exsag.) preglabellar length than other species of the genus; anterior border comes to a point on midline. Moderately sized pygidium with three axial rings.
</paragraph>
